---
// Acknowledgement banner. Above the fold, above the nav. The first
// paragraph names the paper before anything else on the page; the
// demo follows below.
---

<header class="border-b hairline bg-[var(--color-page-dark)]">
  <div class="container-wide pt-14 pb-12 md:pt-20 md:pb-16">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-5">A companion site to a reimplementation of IncPy</p>
    <h1 class="h-display max-w-[22ch]">
      Reading IncPy (Guo &amp; Engler, 2011) alongside rote — the same design, rebuilt for Python today.
    </h1>
    <p class="lede mt-6">
      Every figure, table, and design claim in the paper paired with the corresponding behaviour
      of <code>rote</code>, a pure-Python reimplementation. The core idea is theirs; what changed
      is the platform underneath. Numbers come from <code>bench/results/</code>; sections cite the
      paper they reference.
    </p>
  </div>
</header>
<nav
  class="sticky top-0 z-20 border-b hairline bg-[color:var(--color-page)]/85 backdrop-blur-sm"
  aria-label="Section nav"
>
  <div class="container-wide flex items-center justify-between py-3">
    <a href="#top" class="eyebrow no-underline">rote · paper companion</a>
    <ul class="hidden gap-6 text-[0.86rem] text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] md:flex">
      <li><a href="#loop" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rote)]">Edit-rerun</a></li>
      <li><a href="#delta" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rote)]">Where rote differs</a></li>
      <li><a href="#speed" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rote)]">Speedups</a></li>
      <li><a href="#serializer" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rote)]">Serializers</a></li>
      <li><a href="#graph" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rote)]">Call graph</a></li>
      <li><a href="#gates" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rote)]">Purity</a></li>
      <li><a href="#try" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rote)]">Live editor</a></li>
    </ul>
    <a
      href="https://github.com/puppyum/rote"
      class="pill hover:bg-white/70"
      aria-label="Open the rote repository on GitHub"
    >
      puppyum/rote
    </a>
  </div>
</nav>
